WEBVTT

00:00.467 --> 00:01.667
hy
<i> of you, Sara.</i>

00:01.802 --> 00:03.669
- You're engaged
to be married, John.

00:03.804 --> 00:05.804
<i> [tense music]</i>

00:05.806 --> 00:08.874
<i> - A boy in your care</i>
<i> tried to strangle himself.</i>

00:08.876 --> 00:11.410
You, Dr. Kreizler,
are suspended by the state

00:11.546 --> 00:13.012
from practicing medicine.

00:13.147 --> 00:15.280
- Goo Goo Knox was feeding
from her.

00:15.416 --> 00:17.082
<i> - You found the Linares baby.</i>

00:17.218 --> 00:18.351
The job's done.
<i> - [screams]</i>

00:18.485 --> 00:19.752
<i> - If she strikes again,</i>

00:19.887 --> 00:21.420
I'll never be able to shed
the guilt.

00:21.556 --> 00:23.222
<i> Help me find</i>
<i> the Vanderbilt child.</i>

00:23.224 --> 00:24.957
I am the lead detective
on this case.

00:25.092 --> 00:26.692
<i> Dr. Kreizler is most crucial.</i>

00:26.694 --> 00:28.160
<i> I will need him reinstated.</i>

00:28.295 --> 00:31.230
- I will not take orders
from them.

00:31.366 --> 00:32.565
- Libby Hatch.

00:32.700 --> 00:34.167
Who is she,
and where is she from?

00:34.301 --> 00:36.301
- My father,
he had an accident too.

00:36.437 --> 00:39.372
With him, it was a rope
over a bridge.

00:39.506 --> 00:41.574
- "He is survived
by Malorie Hunter

00:41.709 --> 00:44.910
and his daughter,
Elspeth Hunter of Brooklyn."

00:45.046 --> 00:46.445
And where would
Elspeth Hunter go

00:46.581 --> 00:49.648
<i>if she was hunted by</i>
<i>the New York Police Department?</i>

00:49.784 --> 00:50.983
- Brooklyn.

00:51.118 --> 00:58.191
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:32.493 --> 01:35.227
- Where ya going?

01:35.362 --> 01:39.164
- I get word
someone has a proposition,

01:39.300 --> 01:41.100
you two ain't
what comes to mind.

01:41.102 --> 01:46.038
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:46.173 --> 01:47.572
[groans]

01:47.574 --> 01:50.042
- Mr. Byrnes, this is a place
of business.

01:50.177 --> 01:53.712
- And when mine's complete,
I'll be out of yours.

01:53.848 --> 01:56.782
- [groans]

01:56.784 --> 01:58.717
<i> - What do you suppose</i>
<i> he's up to?</i>

01:58.853 --> 02:01.254
- Byrnes?

02:01.388 --> 02:04.323
Drawing blood
all over the city, no doubt.

02:04.325 --> 02:05.658
Why engage in police work

02:05.793 --> 02:08.393
when violence and intimidation
will suffice?

02:08.529 --> 02:10.595
- He's treating this as a race.

02:10.597 --> 02:12.397
- Against time or against me?

02:12.399 --> 02:14.667
- Oh, more the latter,
I suspect.

02:14.802 --> 02:18.804
Although you do encourage
the competition.

02:18.806 --> 02:19.939
- Me?

02:20.074 --> 02:21.274
- Oh, come now.

02:21.408 --> 02:22.808
You enjoy provoking him.

02:22.943 --> 02:24.343
You're a provocateur.

02:24.345 --> 02:27.280
Even I have not been spared
that.

02:27.414 --> 02:29.682
- Sergeant Kelly.
I'm Sara How--

02:29.817 --> 02:32.885
- Sara Howard of the renowned
Howard Detective Agency.

02:33.020 --> 02:34.219
Welcome to Brooklyn.

02:34.221 --> 02:35.488
Is this your footman?

02:35.623 --> 02:37.690
- John Moore
of "The New York Times."

02:37.825 --> 02:39.158
- A newsman.

02:39.160 --> 02:41.360
It's intriguing pairing
for a detective, Miss Howard.

02:41.362 --> 02:42.961
- We're not all scoundrels,
Sergeant.

02:42.963 --> 02:44.830
- I'll have to take you
at your word.

02:44.965 --> 02:48.033
So this madwoman of yours,
she has ties to Brooklyn.

02:48.169 --> 02:50.235
- Have you reviewed the case?
- There's no need.

02:50.371 --> 02:52.505
A suicide like that,
you remember.

02:52.640 --> 02:54.307
Near took his head clean off.

02:54.441 --> 02:57.242
- We suspect that man may have
been her father.

02:57.244 --> 02:58.978
- Do you know what became
of the wife and child?

02:58.980 --> 03:00.179
- I didn't follow up,
I'm afraid,

03:00.315 --> 03:01.647
but I have a hard time seeing

03:01.782 --> 03:03.448
how that girl could've grown
into your killer.

03:03.450 --> 03:04.583
- Why?
- Good family.

03:04.719 --> 03:06.385
Lived just off Prospect Park.

03:06.387 --> 03:08.521
- Family of means.
- Yeah, very much so.

03:08.656 --> 03:10.923
The girl was proper.
She did as she was told.

03:11.058 --> 03:12.725
Not the killing kind.

03:12.860 --> 03:15.328
- Perhaps she wasn't then.
Not yet.

03:15.462 --> 03:16.996
But given what she's
capable of now,

03:17.131 --> 03:19.999
it stands to reason
she's been in trouble before.

03:20.134 --> 03:21.400
Do you mind if we have a look?

03:21.402 --> 03:23.002
- After you.

03:23.137 --> 03:25.604
- I swear,

03:25.606 --> 03:27.340
I don't know where he is.

03:27.474 --> 03:30.743
[breathing heavily]

03:30.878 --> 03:32.745
Goo Goo doesn't tell me shit.

03:32.880 --> 03:35.681
- Well, he's not an idiot.

03:35.683 --> 03:37.216
But is he reasonable?

03:37.352 --> 03:38.684
- Reasonable?

03:38.819 --> 03:41.153
- Does he have a price?

03:41.288 --> 03:43.155
- Every man has a price.

03:43.290 --> 03:49.362
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:49.496 --> 03:51.364
- For the baby.

03:51.498 --> 03:53.899
Safely returned.

03:53.901 --> 03:56.169
I don't care
what happens to the girl.

03:56.303 --> 03:59.105
Nor to him.

03:59.974 --> 04:01.574
There's more
where that came from,

04:01.709 --> 04:05.310
once the child is delivered
to me unharmed.

04:05.446 --> 04:07.046
Do you get what I'm saying?

04:07.048 --> 04:12.451
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:12.587 --> 04:15.388
Do you get what I'm saying?

04:15.522 --> 04:19.124
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:19.126 --> 04:20.393
- Yes.

04:20.527 --> 04:25.931
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:25.933 --> 04:28.067
- Looks like you were on
to something.

04:30.805 --> 04:32.805
- Elspeth Hunter.

04:32.940 --> 04:35.408
Confined at Blackwell's Island
Asylum for two years.

04:35.542 --> 04:38.543
- What?
Why?

04:38.545 --> 04:39.945
- For attempted murder.

04:40.081 --> 04:43.215
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:43.350 --> 04:44.483
Of her own mother.

04:44.619 --> 04:47.486
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:47.622 --> 04:50.489
<i> [dark music]</i>

04:50.625 --> 04:57.563
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:19.253 --> 05:22.121
<i> [playful French music]</i>

05:22.256 --> 05:27.192
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:27.328 --> 05:28.527
- I received a letter

05:28.663 --> 05:31.464
from the Institute
of Psychology in Vienna.

05:31.599 --> 05:34.533
It is the first medical faculty
of its kind

05:34.535 --> 05:35.668
to include our field,

05:35.803 --> 05:37.603
all tremendously exciting.

05:37.738 --> 05:40.339
They have offered me
a position.

05:40.475 --> 05:43.142
I would depart in two weeks.

05:43.144 --> 05:44.143
Thank you.

05:44.279 --> 05:47.546
- So you're taking it?

05:47.548 --> 05:51.484
- Unless you know of a reason
I shouldn't.

05:51.618 --> 05:53.686
[laughter]

05:53.821 --> 06:00.893
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:08.435 --> 06:11.436
- [laughs]
[slaps]

06:11.438 --> 06:12.638
- [sighs contentedly]
- [laughs]

06:12.773 --> 06:14.707
- Alice, thank you
for taking the time.

06:14.842 --> 06:17.176
I'd like you to meet
a colleague of mine.

06:17.312 --> 06:19.312
Alice, this is Dr. Kreizler.

06:19.446 --> 06:21.046
- What's his pleasure?

06:21.048 --> 06:23.516
- His interest is purely
scientific.

06:23.651 --> 06:25.450
- So you like to watch.

06:25.452 --> 06:28.187
- Observation is the best form
of instruction.

06:28.189 --> 06:30.723
- Next to practice, of course.

06:31.859 --> 06:34.994
Alice has been running
this alternative club

06:35.129 --> 06:36.329
for some time.

06:36.463 --> 06:40.799
- May I inquire as to your
preferred predilection?

06:40.935 --> 06:42.134
- Not so much a predilection

06:42.269 --> 06:45.070
as a manner of existence,
Dr. Kreizler.

06:45.206 --> 06:49.175
- Alice has both male
and female reproductive organs.

06:51.946 --> 06:53.812
Alice's partner Rose
has a fixation

06:53.948 --> 06:57.149
identical to that
of your kidnapper.

06:57.284 --> 06:59.084
- Can you tell me about her?

06:59.086 --> 07:02.488
- Her desires
sometimes torment her.

07:03.758 --> 07:07.626
She seems so lost at times.

07:07.628 --> 07:11.964
It is as if she gains life
by suckling me.

07:12.099 --> 07:14.433
I feel I am her only connection
to the world.

07:14.569 --> 07:16.501
- May I ask,
was Rose abandoned,

07:16.503 --> 07:18.103
and if so, at what age?

07:18.105 --> 07:19.705
- She was 4.

07:19.707 --> 07:21.440
Left on a doorstep
by her mother.

07:21.576 --> 07:22.908
- Abandonment is a trigger

07:22.910 --> 07:25.044
for a host
of psychological ailments.

07:25.179 --> 07:26.245
- Ailments?

07:26.247 --> 07:29.248
- He means
behavioral variations.

07:29.384 --> 07:31.851
- Excuse me for a moment.

07:34.389 --> 07:35.721
- Decreased engagement

07:35.856 --> 07:38.257
coupled with persistent
compulsive drives.

07:38.259 --> 07:40.525
- And a desperation to recreate
profound bonds

07:40.527 --> 07:43.929
that she has been denied
for herself.

07:43.931 --> 07:46.665
It suggests a detachment
from other human beings,

07:46.667 --> 07:48.267
a loneliness,

07:48.269 --> 07:50.403
sated by obsession.

07:50.537 --> 07:53.406
<i> [foreboding music]</i>

07:53.540 --> 07:56.341
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:56.477 --> 07:59.344
[baby cooing]

07:59.480 --> 08:03.416
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:03.550 --> 08:06.752
- The water looks so calm.

08:06.754 --> 08:09.221
That's where we should go.

08:09.356 --> 08:11.156
We should climb aboard
one of those big ships

08:11.292 --> 08:13.358
and see
where the wind takes us.

08:13.494 --> 08:17.763
<i> [soft music]</i>

08:17.765 --> 08:20.565
Nothing is beyond our means,

08:20.567 --> 08:23.235
if we want it enough.

08:23.370 --> 08:29.041
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:29.176 --> 08:30.776
- Stay off the streets
until I get back.

08:30.911 --> 08:32.044
Folks know your face,

08:32.179 --> 08:33.512
and the Pinkertons are out
looking.

08:33.648 --> 08:35.781
[baby cooing]

08:35.783 --> 08:38.451
- [whispering]
Don't worry.

08:38.585 --> 08:40.253
I'll save you some.

08:40.387 --> 08:44.189
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:44.325 --> 08:47.192
<i> [tense music]</i>

08:47.328 --> 08:50.195
[crowd chatting]

08:50.331 --> 08:57.236
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:11.953 --> 09:14.219
- Look who climbed out
of his hidey-hole.

09:14.221 --> 09:17.290
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:17.424 --> 09:19.292
- I need our boys to do
a collection.

09:19.426 --> 09:22.027
- We just did one.

09:22.029 --> 09:25.298
- Well, do another one.

09:25.432 --> 09:27.766
All customers paying
two months ahead,

09:27.902 --> 09:30.635
on my orders.

09:30.637 --> 09:32.637
And you meet me tomorrow
with the money.

09:32.639 --> 09:33.772
- Sure.

09:33.774 --> 09:37.242
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:37.378 --> 09:40.445
Listen, that Doyle...

09:40.447 --> 09:43.983
came about with some old cop
offering money for the baby.

09:43.985 --> 09:45.718
- What?
How much?

09:45.853 --> 09:53.025
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:56.263 --> 09:58.197
- More where that came from,
he said.

09:58.333 --> 09:59.664
- For the baby?

09:59.666 --> 10:02.134
- Sound like you and the girl
are off the hook,

10:02.269 --> 10:04.870
supposing you take him up
on the arrangement.

10:05.006 --> 10:07.206
Kid must belong to someone
important.

10:07.342 --> 10:11.276
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:11.278 --> 10:13.078
Hey.

10:13.080 --> 10:15.080
What about a finder's fee?

10:15.082 --> 10:16.682
A token for my honesty.

10:16.684 --> 10:21.086
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:21.222 --> 10:23.622
- Now that's for your honesty.

10:23.758 --> 10:24.823
You don't wanna see betrayal.

10:24.959 --> 10:29.028
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:29.163 --> 10:30.495
- I have studied these books

10:30.631 --> 10:32.965
in the hope of unlocking
aspects of the inner life

10:33.100 --> 10:37.302
that people cannot
or dare not give voice to.

10:37.304 --> 10:38.904
Paraphilia,

10:39.040 --> 10:42.174
inversion, perversion,

10:42.309 --> 10:44.377
urning, dioning,

10:44.511 --> 10:45.844
all of these I knew,

10:45.980 --> 10:47.846
the way one can know
the features of the moon

10:47.848 --> 10:48.914
through a telescope,

10:48.916 --> 10:50.249
but we may never know

10:50.251 --> 10:53.185
what its surface feels like
to touch.

10:53.320 --> 10:55.588
I understand more
from walking into that room

10:55.723 --> 10:57.190
than Krafft-Ebing

10:57.324 --> 10:59.925
or Havelock Ellis
could have ever taught me

10:59.927 --> 11:01.060
in a hundred volumes.

11:01.062 --> 11:02.261
And I call myself an alienist

11:02.397 --> 11:04.663
without having reckoned
with this.

11:04.665 --> 11:08.067
Perhaps I deserve
having my license taken away.

11:08.202 --> 11:11.237
- That is your conclusion
from the experience?

11:12.607 --> 11:14.407
Dare say, Laszlo,

11:14.541 --> 11:17.542
your mind may be
the most foreign of all.

11:17.544 --> 11:20.613
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:20.748 --> 11:22.882
- The club.

11:23.017 --> 11:24.483
Have you been there before?

11:24.485 --> 11:28.421
- Are you asking professionally
or personally?

11:30.357 --> 11:33.892
I like to keep my mind open
to new experiences.

11:33.894 --> 11:37.562
New feelings.

11:37.564 --> 11:40.565
[phone ringing]

11:40.567 --> 11:47.507
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:48.443 --> 11:50.909
- Hello?

11:50.911 --> 11:52.978
Sara, please, slow down.

11:53.114 --> 11:54.513
- Mister!
- Spare change?

11:54.515 --> 11:55.648
- Get outta here.

11:55.783 --> 11:56.649
Get outta here!

11:56.784 --> 12:00.653
[children chatting]

12:00.788 --> 12:01.921
[children shouting]

12:02.056 --> 12:03.322
- It's hard to tell

12:03.324 --> 12:04.990
whether he's being playful
or barbaric.

12:05.126 --> 12:06.391
- Get outta here,
you little urchin.

12:06.527 --> 12:07.793
Get, get, get!

12:07.928 --> 12:11.596
- With Byrnes, I think
it's best to assume the worst.

12:11.598 --> 12:13.132
Are you quite sure
we had to invite him?

12:13.268 --> 12:14.533
- Before I shoot
the lot of youse!

12:14.669 --> 12:17.370
- We agreed
to keep each other informed.

12:18.940 --> 12:23.342
- Has he told you
what he's been up to?

12:23.344 --> 12:24.877
I thought as much.

12:30.485 --> 12:31.684
- What?

12:31.819 --> 12:33.618
<i> [soft music]</i>

12:33.620 --> 12:34.753
What is it?

12:34.755 --> 12:37.823
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:37.958 --> 12:40.359
- Have you thought
about what it means for us?

12:42.297 --> 12:43.962
- I've thought of nothing else.

12:43.964 --> 12:49.502
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:49.637 --> 12:50.836
He's here.

12:50.838 --> 12:54.039
<i> [tense music]</i>

12:54.041 --> 12:58.377
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:58.379 --> 13:00.045
- Well, who better
to track someone

13:00.181 --> 13:04.049
responsible for endangering
the life of a child?

13:04.185 --> 13:05.851
- Byrnes is pleased
that I've summoned you.

13:05.853 --> 13:07.052
- Shall we?

13:07.188 --> 13:08.653
I have an engagement
this evening.

13:08.655 --> 13:15.394
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:27.608 --> 13:29.408
- Mrs. Malorie Hunter.

13:29.544 --> 13:32.077
We have some questions
about your daughter.

13:32.213 --> 13:34.013
- I read the papers.

13:34.015 --> 13:36.082
I've been expecting you.

13:39.888 --> 13:42.855
<i> [tense music]</i>

13:42.991 --> 13:47.259
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:47.261 --> 13:50.529
- Well, that's a nice
little place, isn't it?

13:50.531 --> 13:52.130
- Aspirations.

13:52.266 --> 13:55.067
- Mrs. Hunter, you must have
some idea where she might be.

13:55.069 --> 13:56.869
- I've no idea where she is.

13:56.871 --> 13:59.005
I haven't seen Elspeth
in years.

13:59.139 --> 14:01.473
This is all I have left of her.

14:01.475 --> 14:03.742
- Does she have
any other family in the city?

14:03.878 --> 14:05.211
- No.

14:05.346 --> 14:07.213
- Friends?

14:07.348 --> 14:08.947
Someone she might turn to
for help?

14:08.949 --> 14:10.616
Places she might go?

14:10.751 --> 14:12.150
- I wouldn't know.

14:12.286 --> 14:16.755
It was just the two of us
after her father's...

14:16.757 --> 14:18.490
accident.

14:18.626 --> 14:20.426
Elspeth was the perfect child.

14:20.561 --> 14:22.761
She never gave me any trouble
at all.

14:22.897 --> 14:24.096
She went to school
with children

14:24.098 --> 14:26.032
from the finest families
in Brooklyn,

14:26.166 --> 14:29.301
as clever as any of them,
and she was a beautiful dancer.

14:29.303 --> 14:30.836
We lived in Paris for a year.

14:30.971 --> 14:32.304
Studied at the school
of ballet.

14:32.440 --> 14:34.841
- Why do you suspect
your husband killed himself,

14:34.975 --> 14:36.642
Mrs. Hunter?

14:36.777 --> 14:40.112
- How am I to know?

14:40.248 --> 14:42.048
He had a nervous disposition.

14:42.182 --> 14:43.782
- Was he under the care
of a doctor?

14:43.784 --> 14:46.652
- Not that I was aware of.

14:46.787 --> 14:47.853
He was raised in the country.

14:47.988 --> 14:49.722
The city made him
uncomfortable.

14:49.857 --> 14:51.590
Perhaps he'd simply had enough.

14:51.726 --> 14:53.926
- I imagine it was difficult
for a man from the country

14:54.062 --> 14:55.394
to maintain the lifestyle

14:55.396 --> 14:58.196
to which you had become
accustomed.

14:58.198 --> 15:00.466
- Why do you think
your daughter attacked you?

15:00.601 --> 15:01.934
Had she been violent before?

15:01.936 --> 15:03.536
- Not that I recall.

15:03.671 --> 15:06.338
- You told the police
she tried to kill you.

15:06.340 --> 15:10.476
Something prompted her
to act so aggressively.

15:10.611 --> 15:14.012
- A fight, perhaps?

15:14.014 --> 15:15.281
Over the baby?

15:15.416 --> 15:22.388
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:23.291 --> 15:26.092
You might as well tell us
everything.

15:27.495 --> 15:30.496
- It was a girl.

15:30.631 --> 15:31.898
- Where is she now?

15:32.032 --> 15:35.101
- The Children's Aid Society
took responsibility.

15:35.235 --> 15:36.902
Elspeth didn't have
the capacity--

15:37.037 --> 15:38.504
- Because she was still a child
herself.

15:38.639 --> 15:39.638
- She was unstable.

15:39.774 --> 15:41.974
Incapable of being a mother.

15:41.976 --> 15:43.442
She couldn't care for it.

15:43.577 --> 15:46.178
- So you took the child
against Elspeth's wishes.

15:46.314 --> 15:48.514
- She came at me with a knife.

15:48.649 --> 15:51.850
I was fortunate to escape
with my life.

15:51.852 --> 15:53.452
- That's the story
you told the police.

15:53.454 --> 15:56.923
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:57.057 --> 15:58.524
But that's not
what really happened,

15:58.659 --> 16:01.393
is it, Mrs. Hunter?

16:01.529 --> 16:03.195
She never touched you.

16:03.331 --> 16:04.997
- Are you calling me a liar?

16:05.133 --> 16:07.199
- You were a woman of means.

16:07.335 --> 16:09.135
The Children's Aid Society
wouldn't take the baby

16:09.269 --> 16:10.469
unless you could prove

16:10.471 --> 16:12.070
your daughter was a danger
to it.

16:12.072 --> 16:13.672
Otherwise,
they were your responsibility.

16:13.674 --> 16:15.607
And that's the last thing
you wanted.

16:15.609 --> 16:17.209
- How dare you?

16:17.345 --> 16:19.278
- So you fabricated a story
about her trying to kill you.

16:19.413 --> 16:21.480
You inflicted a profound trauma
on your daughter

16:21.482 --> 16:23.950
from which she never recovered.

16:24.084 --> 16:27.285
You abandoned her,
you abandoned her child,

16:27.287 --> 16:28.887
and you created a killer.

16:29.023 --> 16:32.424
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:32.426 --> 16:34.493
- I didn't know
what would happen.

16:34.495 --> 16:36.629
- Of course you did.

16:36.764 --> 16:38.831
It gave you back your freedom.

16:38.833 --> 16:41.633
The freedom you had
since your husband's death.

16:41.635 --> 16:44.436
You didn't have to care
for anyone now.

16:44.438 --> 16:45.437
Not the baby,

16:45.573 --> 16:47.840
nor the daughter
you drove insane.

16:47.842 --> 16:49.708
- I was doing what was best.

16:49.710 --> 16:50.977
- For her?

16:51.111 --> 16:53.646
Or for you?

16:53.781 --> 16:55.914
You failed her then.

16:55.916 --> 16:58.985
But you can help us now.

16:59.119 --> 17:02.655
Does Elspeth know
where the child is?

17:02.790 --> 17:03.789
- No.

17:03.924 --> 17:06.659
[sobbing]

17:06.794 --> 17:09.228
I never told her.

17:11.065 --> 17:12.931
I have the papers.

17:12.933 --> 17:14.132
From the orphanage.

17:14.268 --> 17:20.939
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:20.941 --> 17:23.141
- My God, Laszlo.

17:23.277 --> 17:24.743
- Do you think
Libby's come back to Brooklyn

17:24.879 --> 17:25.878
to find her daughter?

17:26.014 --> 17:27.279
- I don't know.

17:27.415 --> 17:29.147
But the child is in
great danger either way.

17:29.149 --> 17:30.949
- If Libby Hatch didn't attack
her mother,

17:30.951 --> 17:34.220
how'd she get the scar
on her face?

17:34.355 --> 17:36.022
- She gave it to herself.

17:36.156 --> 17:40.092
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:40.228 --> 17:43.095
[baby cooing]

17:43.231 --> 17:49.035
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:49.169 --> 17:52.504
- I got you something.

17:52.640 --> 17:54.907
- [laughs]

18:03.051 --> 18:05.984
- Gets cold at night
on them ocean liners.

18:06.120 --> 18:07.920
- You mean it?

18:09.257 --> 18:10.923
- I found our way out
of this mess.

18:10.925 --> 18:12.524
- [laughs]

18:12.660 --> 18:15.327
- Vanderbilt's offering
a reward.

18:15.463 --> 18:17.063
All we gotta do
is give up the baby

18:17.197 --> 18:20.933
and we're on the next ship out.

18:20.935 --> 18:24.670
- You'd sell him?
You'd sell our baby?

18:24.805 --> 18:26.405
He's our baby!

18:26.407 --> 18:28.140
- The damn Pinkertons
are after you.

18:28.142 --> 18:29.675
They're not gonna stop, Libby!

18:29.810 --> 18:30.877
- No.

18:31.011 --> 18:32.745
- You stole
a goddamn Vanderbilt!

18:32.747 --> 18:34.146
- No!

18:34.282 --> 18:35.748
[baby crying]

18:35.750 --> 18:38.617
- You know he's gonna end up
like the rest of 'em.

18:38.753 --> 18:40.887
Might as well get something
for him while we can.

18:41.021 --> 18:42.288
- No.

18:44.492 --> 18:46.625
No.

18:46.627 --> 18:47.826
[grunts]

18:47.828 --> 18:50.829
[baby crying]

18:50.831 --> 18:53.699
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:53.834 --> 18:56.235
- I'm doing this for you.

18:56.370 --> 19:00.839
- [sobbing]
No, no, no!

19:00.975 --> 19:04.843
[sobbing]

19:04.845 --> 19:06.445
No!

19:06.447 --> 19:10.248
- Her name is Clara.

19:10.250 --> 19:13.452
For her own grandmother
to make her an orphan...

19:13.587 --> 19:16.188
are you not at least curious
to meet the girl?

19:16.190 --> 19:18.324
- Our presence would do
more damage than good.

19:18.459 --> 19:20.993
We'd be upending her already
delicate world order.

19:20.995 --> 19:22.595
These records will have to do.

19:22.730 --> 19:25.063
[door opens]

19:25.199 --> 19:27.466
- Gentlemen.

19:27.468 --> 19:29.267
- You brought them.
Good.

19:29.269 --> 19:31.403
- Is there cause
to reexamine them?

19:31.539 --> 19:33.139
- Libby's mother reignited
my interest.

19:33.274 --> 19:35.474
They may contain a clue
to her whereabouts.

19:35.609 --> 19:38.277
- This is the first memory box
Libby constructed.

19:38.412 --> 19:40.146
Deterioration
of the photographs tells us

19:40.281 --> 19:42.280
it's older than the others.

19:42.282 --> 19:45.217
- I remember.
Her first victim.

19:45.219 --> 19:48.154
- The child in the photograph
is not a victim.

19:48.288 --> 19:49.755
I suspect it's the daughter.

19:49.890 --> 19:51.624
- Libby mourned her
when her mother took her away

19:51.759 --> 19:52.891
as if she were dead.

19:53.027 --> 19:54.760
- Do you think she knows
where the girl is now?

19:54.895 --> 19:55.962
- No.

19:56.096 --> 19:57.563
Assuming we believe
Mrs. Hunter.

19:57.698 --> 19:58.965
- If Libby knew
where her daughter was,

19:59.099 --> 20:00.232
she would've retrieved her.

20:00.368 --> 20:01.767
There would be no need
to recreate her

20:01.902 --> 20:02.768
with these other children.

20:02.903 --> 20:04.637
- "Recreate her."

20:04.639 --> 20:06.172
- That's a disturbing thought.

20:06.306 --> 20:13.379
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:36.804 --> 20:38.937
- He said he'd be here.

20:39.073 --> 20:40.472
I ain't lying to you.

20:40.474 --> 20:42.274
- Next time you see him,
I have a message

20:42.410 --> 20:43.942
I'd like you to relay.

20:43.944 --> 20:48.747
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:48.883 --> 20:50.016
- [groans]

20:50.150 --> 20:53.019
[grunting]

20:53.153 --> 21:00.326
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:04.432 --> 21:06.164
- I propose a different course.

21:06.300 --> 21:07.966
- A<i> different</i>
different course?

21:07.968 --> 21:09.902
- We've learned
that the madwoman had a child

21:09.904 --> 21:11.169
of her own,

21:11.305 --> 21:13.972
one that was ripped from her
unceremoniously.

21:13.974 --> 21:16.174
- So Kreizler was correct
in his assessment?

21:16.176 --> 21:18.644
- Begrudgingly so, I admit.
Yes, sir.

21:18.779 --> 21:21.047
He believes
that this is the root cause

21:21.181 --> 21:22.849
of her baby-stealing,
as it were.

21:22.983 --> 21:24.316
I intend to put this
to the test

21:24.452 --> 21:26.719
by means of luring Libby Hatch
from her hiding.

21:26.854 --> 21:28.454
- If I know where you're going
with this,

21:28.589 --> 21:30.989
Vanderbilt will hate us for it.

21:31.125 --> 21:33.392
But...

21:33.394 --> 21:36.528
he'll have his baby back
in the end.

21:36.530 --> 21:38.731
How much
is this going to cost me?

21:38.733 --> 21:45.705
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:48.542 --> 21:50.543
- I have a proposal.

21:50.678 --> 21:53.513
On behalf
of Mr. Cornelius Vanderbilt.

21:59.286 --> 22:02.187
<i> [soft ambient music]</i>

22:02.189 --> 22:09.262
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:20.541 --> 22:21.807
- Laszlo.

22:21.943 --> 22:23.209
I apologize.

22:23.344 --> 22:26.746
It was not my intention
to intrude upon you.

22:26.880 --> 22:28.280
- Didn't want to wake you.

22:28.416 --> 22:32.618
Sleep is a rare commodity
for us both these days.

22:32.620 --> 22:35.087
I phoned John to let him know
where you were.

22:35.222 --> 22:36.622
I hope you don't mind.

22:36.758 --> 22:39.024
- Of course not.

22:39.160 --> 22:42.962
That was very courteous of you.

22:43.097 --> 22:44.696
Did he say anything?

22:44.832 --> 22:47.566
- Only mumbled about extremes
you're willing to go

22:47.701 --> 22:50.369
to avoid either confrontation
or conversation.

22:50.504 --> 22:52.905
I forget which.

22:53.040 --> 22:55.041
- Both apply.

22:56.110 --> 22:58.110
- If you'd like
to talk about it...

22:58.245 --> 23:00.112
- I would not.

23:00.247 --> 23:01.847
- Would it help
if I already knew

23:01.849 --> 23:05.451
what it was concerning?

23:05.453 --> 23:07.719
- No.

23:07.721 --> 23:10.856
<i> [tense music]</i>

23:10.858 --> 23:13.259
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:13.394 --> 23:16.229
- There must be a clue
in these boxes.

23:18.332 --> 23:21.200
Libby's mother
is a very interesting woman.

23:21.335 --> 23:24.870
She lacks empathy,
even for her own daughter.

23:24.872 --> 23:26.071
Why choose to have a child

23:26.073 --> 23:27.473
if that was not
what she wanted?

23:27.609 --> 23:31.143
- Perhaps she genuinely
believed herself capable.

23:31.145 --> 23:33.545
- Or she felt pressured.

23:33.681 --> 23:36.348
It is a woman's purpose,
after all.

23:36.350 --> 23:43.256
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:44.158 --> 23:46.626
- You ready?

23:46.760 --> 23:48.360
Come on ahead.

23:48.362 --> 23:54.500
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:54.502 --> 23:55.901
- [laughs nervously]
- Great.

23:56.037 --> 23:57.369
Hold it.

23:57.505 --> 24:01.307
Perfect.
Like you're showing her around.

24:01.309 --> 24:02.642
This way, Miss.

24:02.776 --> 24:05.444
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:05.579 --> 24:07.179
Let's get one by her new bed.

24:07.315 --> 24:14.420
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:21.996 --> 24:23.462
[baby crying]

24:23.597 --> 24:24.730
- Libby?

24:32.874 --> 24:34.507
[shushes]

24:41.148 --> 24:42.214
Stop!
Stop!

24:42.216 --> 24:44.684
No!

24:44.818 --> 24:46.418
No.
- [grunting]

24:46.420 --> 24:49.488
- [grunts]
- [breathing heavily]

24:49.623 --> 24:50.890
[yelps]

24:51.025 --> 24:52.224
- Let go, damn it!

24:52.226 --> 24:53.625
[grunts]
- [screams]

24:53.761 --> 24:55.961
- I'm sorry I took him,
but I couldn't do it.

24:55.963 --> 24:57.296
- I hate you.

24:57.431 --> 24:58.430
I hate you!

24:58.566 --> 25:00.165
You're just like the rest
of them.

25:00.167 --> 25:02.101
- No!
I came back for you.

25:02.236 --> 25:03.769
- [grunts]
- [screams]

25:03.905 --> 25:06.238
[both breathing heavily]

25:06.374 --> 25:08.107
- [screams]

25:08.242 --> 25:09.909
- Libby, I came back for you.

25:10.044 --> 25:13.713
[baby crying]

25:13.847 --> 25:16.048
And our boy.

25:16.183 --> 25:18.518
I came back for our boy.

25:18.652 --> 25:19.719
Huh?

25:19.853 --> 25:21.120
We're a family.

25:21.255 --> 25:23.789
[baby crying]
- [sobbing]

25:23.925 --> 25:25.190
- Huh?

25:25.192 --> 25:29.261
- [sobbing]
Our boy.

25:29.397 --> 25:30.730
- I think he's hungry.

25:30.864 --> 25:33.733
[baby crying]

25:33.867 --> 25:36.736
<i> [tense music]</i>

25:36.870 --> 25:39.805
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:39.807 --> 25:41.207
- Such a good boy.

25:41.342 --> 25:44.476
Oh, such a good boy!

25:44.478 --> 25:46.878
Oh, such a good boy.

25:46.880 --> 25:47.947
[sighs]

25:48.082 --> 25:49.881
[baby crying]

25:50.017 --> 25:52.351
Such a good boy.

25:52.486 --> 25:55.254
[sighs]
[laughs]

25:58.159 --> 25:59.358
What is this?

25:59.493 --> 26:06.566
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:09.904 --> 26:11.103
What is this?

26:11.105 --> 26:13.839
[baby fussing]

26:13.975 --> 26:15.907
- It's about your daughter.

26:15.909 --> 26:17.243
I'm sorry.

26:17.378 --> 26:20.912
- [sobbing]
What is this?

26:20.914 --> 26:23.482
[baby crying]

26:25.052 --> 26:25.918
- Where have you been?

26:26.053 --> 26:28.454
- It was a long night.

26:28.589 --> 26:30.990
- If I were you,
I'd expect another one.

26:31.125 --> 26:33.525
- Why?
What's happened?

26:33.527 --> 26:38.063
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:38.199 --> 26:39.598
That bastard.

26:39.733 --> 26:41.333
<i> He's gone behind my back</i>

26:41.335 --> 26:43.335
<i> and used that child</i>
<i> to lure Libby out of hiding,</i>

26:43.337 --> 26:46.271
<i> and your fiancée's father</i>
<i> aids him in the deceit.</i>

26:46.273 --> 26:47.807
- Vanderbilt must've
endorsed it.

26:47.941 --> 26:49.141
- I hope
you're not defending them.

26:49.276 --> 26:50.676
- Of course not.

26:50.812 --> 26:52.478
I'm simply trying to deduce
the sequence of events

26:52.614 --> 26:54.013
so neither of us goes off
half-cocked.

26:54.148 --> 26:56.883
<i> - Oh, I intend to--</i>
- Sara, take a breath.

26:58.352 --> 27:00.419
<i> Have you spoken with Laszlo?</i>

27:00.554 --> 27:02.488
- He's on his way
to pick me up.

27:02.490 --> 27:04.423
We're headed back to Brooklyn
to see if we can wrestle

27:04.558 --> 27:05.825
<i> the poor child</i>
<i> from their clutches.</i>

27:05.959 --> 27:08.294
- I shall deal with Hearst
myself.

27:08.429 --> 27:09.695
There's another conversation

27:09.697 --> 27:11.697
I've been meaning to have
with him anyway.

27:11.833 --> 27:13.365
- Fine.

27:13.367 --> 27:15.468
Wait...

27:16.304 --> 27:17.969
- I shall update you later.

27:17.971 --> 27:20.906
<i> I'll be in touch.</i>

27:20.908 --> 27:22.374
- Perverse?

27:22.510 --> 27:23.976
I don't think
you wanna go down this road

27:24.111 --> 27:25.577
with me, Mr. Moore.

27:25.579 --> 27:28.380
- Is there no outrage
you will not defend

27:28.382 --> 27:29.781
in the name of free press?

27:29.917 --> 27:32.518
- Libby Hatch sells more papers
than the war.

27:32.520 --> 27:33.853
- And what of the child?

27:33.987 --> 27:35.787
Have you no concern
for her wellbeing?

27:35.789 --> 27:37.389
- Well, as far as I can see,

27:37.525 --> 27:39.859
her quality of life is elevated
significantly.

27:39.993 --> 27:42.261
I wish I could say the same
for our beloved Violet,

27:42.396 --> 27:43.595
but ever since she--

27:43.731 --> 27:45.264
- This has nothing to do
with Violet.

27:45.399 --> 27:47.533
- That's the problem, isn't it?

27:47.669 --> 27:50.269
She seems to be of no concern
to you at all.

27:50.404 --> 27:52.404
- You're out of line,
Mr. Hearst.

27:52.406 --> 27:53.539
- Am I?

27:53.541 --> 27:56.542
<i> [tense music]</i>

27:56.544 --> 28:03.549
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:04.018 --> 28:07.219
Your private affairs
are of no concern to me, John,

28:07.221 --> 28:08.954
as long as they remain private.

28:08.956 --> 28:10.556
Unfortunately,
your relationship

28:10.692 --> 28:13.993
with Miss Howard is out there
for all to see.

28:15.829 --> 28:18.097
Now, I say this man to man:

28:18.232 --> 28:19.565
I think we both understand

28:19.701 --> 28:21.701
there's a transactional nature
to your marriage,

28:21.835 --> 28:23.369
as there is with many.

28:23.504 --> 28:26.038
But Violet...

28:26.173 --> 28:28.240
is a lovely young woman,

28:28.376 --> 28:31.711
and I do not wish
to see her hurt.

28:31.845 --> 28:32.845
- Nor do I.

28:35.049 --> 28:37.283
- Then you know
what you have to do.

28:39.053 --> 28:41.521
I must run to a meeting.

28:41.655 --> 28:43.188
Oh,
the whole family is gathering

28:43.190 --> 28:44.456
at Delmonico's tonight

28:44.458 --> 28:46.525
to argue out summer plans
in Newport.

28:46.660 --> 28:48.928
We draw lots for the bedrooms.

28:49.063 --> 28:51.130
It's good fun.

28:51.265 --> 28:52.464
I'll expect to see you there.

28:52.466 --> 28:55.467
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

28:55.469 --> 29:02.608
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:24.966 --> 29:26.365
- You live here?
- We're with Byrnes.

29:26.500 --> 29:27.499
Step aside.

29:27.635 --> 29:31.971
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:32.106 --> 29:34.440
Open the door!

29:34.442 --> 29:36.776
- Shut your bone box.
She could be here any minute.

29:36.911 --> 29:38.778
- Vanderbilt put me in charge
of this case,

29:38.913 --> 29:40.712
and I will now allow you
or Mr. Hearst

29:40.848 --> 29:43.515
to exploit the poor child
in his name or in mine.

29:43.651 --> 29:45.050
- Mrs. Hunter consented
to the plan.

29:45.186 --> 29:46.986
- You said
it was a personal favor

29:47.121 --> 29:48.454
to Mr. Vanderbilt.

29:48.456 --> 29:49.989
- Your granddaughter
is an innocent.

29:50.124 --> 29:52.458
She does not deserve to be
paraded around for the papers,

29:52.460 --> 29:55.394
or used as a lure.

29:55.529 --> 29:58.798
- Clara, you're coming with us.

29:58.932 --> 30:01.400
We'll keep you safe, I promise.

30:01.535 --> 30:02.868
- She's coming.

30:02.870 --> 30:04.670
Spotted three blocks away
in a striped jacket.

30:04.672 --> 30:06.338
Should we pursue?
- No.

30:06.474 --> 30:08.140
Let her come to us.

30:10.411 --> 30:11.743
Results, Miss Howard.

30:11.745 --> 30:13.879
The results will out.

30:14.015 --> 30:20.953
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:25.559 --> 30:28.427
<i> [tense music building]</i>

30:28.562 --> 30:35.735
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:08.870 --> 31:10.736
[knocking on door]

31:10.872 --> 31:12.404
- [whispering]
Don't be nervous, sweetheart.

31:12.540 --> 31:13.739
Just let her in.

31:13.741 --> 31:15.675
The boys'll take her down
in a flash.

31:15.809 --> 31:22.882
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:41.069 --> 31:42.200
- Where'd you get this coat?

31:42.202 --> 31:43.802
- She said I could keep it

31:43.804 --> 31:45.137
if I delivered something
to this address.

31:45.139 --> 31:46.138
- What'd she give you?

31:46.140 --> 31:49.341
<i> [tense music]</i>

31:49.343 --> 31:50.743
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:50.745 --> 31:53.479
- She said to tell you
there was one for each of you.

31:53.614 --> 31:57.483
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:57.618 --> 32:00.486
[bell ringing]

32:00.621 --> 32:05.223
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:05.359 --> 32:07.293
- It was smart
bringing 'em out like that.

32:09.563 --> 32:11.297
- I wanna see her.

32:11.432 --> 32:16.903
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:17.037 --> 32:18.504
- There's too many of them.

32:18.639 --> 32:23.842
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:23.844 --> 32:25.644
Libby, we have to go.

32:25.646 --> 32:32.318
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:32.453 --> 32:34.386
Libby.

32:34.388 --> 32:36.054
Libby.

32:36.056 --> 32:37.255
- There!
Over there!

32:37.257 --> 32:38.457
I see 'em!
Over there!

32:38.592 --> 32:39.592
Go!

32:39.727 --> 32:42.461
[indistinct shouting]

32:42.463 --> 32:49.335
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:50.605 --> 32:51.804
- We should split up.

32:51.806 --> 32:53.071
They'll be looking
for both of us.

32:53.073 --> 32:59.979
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:13.894 --> 33:16.428
[crowd chatting]

33:16.564 --> 33:23.035
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:23.037 --> 33:24.503
- You run along now.

33:24.638 --> 33:31.544
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:45.860 --> 33:47.593
You can come out.

33:47.728 --> 33:54.600
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:56.204 --> 33:57.403
Come on.

33:57.538 --> 34:01.139
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:01.141 --> 34:02.408
Keep coming.

34:02.543 --> 34:07.413
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:07.548 --> 34:08.414
That'll do.

34:08.549 --> 34:11.350
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:11.352 --> 34:14.020
The bullet was a nice touch.

34:14.154 --> 34:16.822
But I got one for you too.

34:16.957 --> 34:18.824
- Tell me something.

34:18.959 --> 34:23.295
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:23.431 --> 34:24.897
[laughs]

34:25.033 --> 34:29.035
My daughter.

34:29.169 --> 34:32.104
What's she like?

34:32.106 --> 34:33.706
- Mute, maybe.

34:33.841 --> 34:35.641
Or plain stupid.

34:35.776 --> 34:40.046
Screwed up in the head
like her mother, I'd imagine.

34:40.180 --> 34:42.048
Now down on your knees.

34:42.182 --> 34:47.853
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:47.988 --> 34:49.187
Vanderbilt's gonna be pleased

34:49.323 --> 34:53.191
when I walk in with you
and that baby.

34:53.327 --> 34:55.061
Real pleased.

34:55.195 --> 34:57.529
Now get your hands
behind your back.

34:57.531 --> 35:04.503
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:09.077 --> 35:12.144
<i> [tense music building]</i>

35:12.280 --> 35:14.813
She's down here!

35:14.815 --> 35:16.214
[splutters]

35:16.350 --> 35:20.887
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:21.021 --> 35:22.688
[splutters]

35:22.823 --> 35:29.695
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:29.830 --> 35:32.698
[children giggling]

35:32.833 --> 35:39.705
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:54.655 --> 35:56.122
- Clara,

35:56.256 --> 35:59.858
I told you about Dr. Stratton.

35:59.860 --> 36:02.728
- Hello, Clara.

36:02.863 --> 36:05.998
- Stevie, would you mind
showing her around?

36:06.134 --> 36:08.134
- Sure.
This way.

36:08.268 --> 36:09.135
- [whispering]
It's all right.

36:09.270 --> 36:12.138
<i> [soft music]</i>

36:12.273 --> 36:17.209
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:17.211 --> 36:19.077
She has a difficult road.

36:19.079 --> 36:21.147
One I won't be able to help her
navigate.

36:21.282 --> 36:23.482
- The loss of your license
is only temporary.

36:23.484 --> 36:25.217
- At least
the institute will remain open

36:25.219 --> 36:26.885
in the interim.

36:27.021 --> 36:29.822
I appreciate your assistance
where that's concerned.

36:29.824 --> 36:32.424
- Of course.

36:32.426 --> 36:35.694
What happens next
with the case?

36:35.830 --> 36:38.297
- More deaths.

36:38.432 --> 36:42.100
Today's events guaranteed it.

36:42.102 --> 36:43.235
- If we're working tonight,

36:43.237 --> 36:45.037
I can cancel my plans
with Lucius.

36:45.173 --> 36:47.105
- No, I insist you keep them.

36:47.241 --> 36:50.108
Give him my best.

36:50.110 --> 36:52.244
- Are you okay, Miss Sara?

36:52.246 --> 36:54.180
You seem out of sorts.

36:54.315 --> 36:55.848
- I'm frustrated.

36:55.984 --> 36:57.916
Furious, truth be told.

36:58.052 --> 36:59.185
After the stunt
Byrnes pulled today,

36:59.320 --> 37:01.787
who knows
what Libby is capable of next.

37:01.922 --> 37:03.455
- I'd rather you not be alone.

37:03.457 --> 37:04.723
Shall I call Mr. Moore?

37:04.725 --> 37:06.058
- No.

37:06.194 --> 37:07.926
- Then I will reschedule
dinner.

37:07.928 --> 37:10.062
- Please, Bitsy.
I'm fine.

37:10.064 --> 37:12.931
But I appreciate your concern.

37:12.933 --> 37:17.135
- If you love him,
you must tell him, Sara.

37:17.137 --> 37:19.005
A time will come
when it's too late.

37:19.139 --> 37:22.008
<i> [somber music]</i>

37:22.142 --> 37:27.013
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:27.147 --> 37:28.814
<i> [refined music]</i>

37:28.949 --> 37:31.617
- Will you wait for Mr. Moore
or shall I take the order?

37:31.752 --> 37:34.020
- There's no need to wait.
He'll be along directly.

37:34.154 --> 37:36.088
- You sure of that, Chief?

37:36.224 --> 37:39.157
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:39.293 --> 37:41.427
- We spoke today as men,
Violet.

37:41.562 --> 37:43.229
That's more than I should have
said on the matter,

37:43.364 --> 37:44.963
but nor will I see you fret.

37:45.099 --> 37:46.899
- I'm not fretting.

37:46.901 --> 37:48.634
Not tonight.

37:48.769 --> 37:51.437
It would sully the whole summer
to plan it with a sour heart.

37:51.572 --> 37:54.640
- The summer
you are to be married, my dear.

37:54.775 --> 37:57.443
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:57.578 --> 37:59.978
Mr. Moore will have
the Vichyssoise to start.

37:59.980 --> 38:00.847
- Very cold.

38:00.981 --> 38:02.381
- And the porterhouse, rare.

38:02.383 --> 38:05.317
- With spinach.

38:05.319 --> 38:07.586
You know his tastes
almost better than I.

38:07.722 --> 38:09.187
[both laugh]

38:09.189 --> 38:12.190
- I well might, darling.

38:12.326 --> 38:15.428
[phone ringing]

38:19.067 --> 38:20.933
- Hello?
<i> - Oh, thank God.</i>

38:20.935 --> 38:23.936
I'm so relieved
to hear your voice.

38:23.938 --> 38:25.404
I've been expecting you.

38:25.539 --> 38:27.005
<i> Kreizler said you left him</i>
<i> hours ago.</i>

38:27.141 --> 38:28.540
- I'm sorry.

38:28.542 --> 38:30.142
There was more work to be done
at the office.

38:30.144 --> 38:32.478
- Have you uncovered
a new lead?

38:33.814 --> 38:35.882
<i> Sara, if you refuse</i>
<i> to speak to me, I--</i>

38:36.016 --> 38:38.216
- I've not refused.

38:38.352 --> 38:40.086
- You have.

38:40.220 --> 38:42.488
And it's unbearable.

38:43.424 --> 38:44.557
- I think you know by now

38:44.692 --> 38:46.224
that I find it
particularly difficult

38:46.360 --> 38:48.294
and I have trouble...

38:48.429 --> 38:51.363
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

38:51.365 --> 38:54.166
<i> - Expressing?</i>

38:54.302 --> 38:56.302
- Yes.
Expressing.

38:56.437 --> 39:01.307
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:01.442 --> 39:04.242
But I thought what we did
was rather wonderful.

39:04.244 --> 39:07.313
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:07.448 --> 39:09.515
- As did I.

39:09.650 --> 39:13.385
<i> - However ill-conceived</i>
<i> it may have been.</i>

39:13.521 --> 39:15.421
- Are you saying you regret it?

39:17.125 --> 39:18.691
- No.

39:21.261 --> 39:22.929
That's not what I meant.

39:24.465 --> 39:27.333
<i> But we did not think it</i>
<i> through.</i>

39:27.468 --> 39:29.135
<i> What it was.</i>

39:29.270 --> 39:32.871
- The question is not what was,
it--

39:33.007 --> 39:35.207
<i> it's what is and...</i>

39:35.209 --> 39:37.476
<i> what will be.</i>

39:37.478 --> 39:39.478
<i> I'm asking what you want.</i>

39:39.480 --> 39:42.748
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:42.883 --> 39:45.351
Damn it, Sara,
I can't do this anymore.

39:45.486 --> 39:47.553
This talking in circles,
it's maddening.

39:47.688 --> 39:48.887
<i> - John.</i>

39:48.889 --> 39:50.422
- I will make a decision
for the both of us

39:50.424 --> 39:51.757
<i> if I must.</i>

39:51.892 --> 39:57.696
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:57.832 --> 40:00.766
Very well.

40:00.901 --> 40:01.767
Good night, Sara.

40:01.902 --> 40:08.875
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:23.457 --> 40:26.325
<i> [ominous music]</i>

40:26.460 --> 40:28.527
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:28.529 --> 40:29.996
Delmonico's.

40:30.130 --> 40:37.003
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:41.942 --> 40:44.810
[phone ringing]

40:44.945 --> 40:51.651
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:57.291 --> 41:00.959
One moment, please.

41:00.961 --> 41:03.962
[phone ringing]

41:03.964 --> 41:10.903
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:15.175 --> 41:17.976
[latch clicks]

41:17.978 --> 41:19.111
[door opens]

41:19.113 --> 41:22.849
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:22.983 --> 41:23.982
- John?

41:24.118 --> 41:31.023
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:34.795 --> 41:38.264
- What have you done

41:38.399 --> 41:39.531
with her?

41:39.533 --> 41:43.903
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:48.342 --> 41:49.809
- Where is she?

41:49.943 --> 41:52.344
- Where is the baby you stole
from the Vanderbilts?

41:52.346 --> 41:55.080
- I didn't steal him.
He's mine.

41:55.216 --> 41:56.548
- Is she yours or is he yours?

41:56.684 --> 41:58.150
- They're both mine.
- Are you sure?

41:58.285 --> 41:59.485
- Stop.

41:59.487 --> 42:00.820
- It's a simple question.

42:00.955 --> 42:03.222
- I saw you...

42:03.357 --> 42:06.626
and that doctor
taking her away.

42:06.760 --> 42:09.629
- Do you want to see her?

42:09.763 --> 42:12.564
Because if you give the baby
back,

42:12.566 --> 42:13.499
then perhaps I can arrange--

42:13.635 --> 42:16.035
- Give him to you?

42:16.170 --> 42:17.303
No.

42:18.306 --> 42:19.639
No.

42:19.773 --> 42:22.842
I'd be charred up
faster than poor Martha Napp.

42:22.976 --> 42:26.578
- Cornelius Vanderbilt
can broker your freedom.

42:26.580 --> 42:28.980
All you have to do
is return the child unharmed.

42:28.982 --> 42:32.652
- He offered us money already,
but we didn't fall for it.

42:32.786 --> 42:36.988
- What I'm offering is a chance
to reunite with Clara.

42:36.990 --> 42:39.791
<i> [tense music]</i>

42:39.793 --> 42:42.094
But you can't keep that baby.

42:44.131 --> 42:46.933
He belongs to someone.

42:48.202 --> 42:51.270
You of all people
must understand that pain.

42:51.405 --> 42:55.541
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:55.543 --> 42:57.476
- You spent time with her.

42:59.947 --> 43:01.614
- Yes.

43:03.617 --> 43:06.786
- That Irish cop,
he said she's like me.

43:09.090 --> 43:11.691
- Doyle?

43:11.825 --> 43:14.026
- I don't know his name.

43:14.161 --> 43:19.365
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:19.367 --> 43:21.033
I slit his throat.

43:23.705 --> 43:26.506
He stained my shirt.

43:26.640 --> 43:29.308
He said that she...

43:29.443 --> 43:33.312
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:33.447 --> 43:36.648
Is she off in the head?

43:36.650 --> 43:39.985
Like her mom?

43:40.121 --> 43:41.587
Can you tell me?

43:44.325 --> 43:46.125
- We're going to help her.

43:46.260 --> 43:48.460
And we can help you too.

43:48.596 --> 43:50.530
- No!

43:50.664 --> 43:53.065
No, no.
[laughs]

43:53.067 --> 43:57.669
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:57.805 --> 44:00.072
You're the one.

44:00.207 --> 44:01.741
You--

44:01.875 --> 44:04.944
you ruined everything.

44:06.480 --> 44:09.048
You stay away from her.

44:11.219 --> 44:13.419
[gunshot]

44:13.554 --> 44:16.689
[both grunting]

44:18.092 --> 44:18.958
[gunshot]

44:19.093 --> 44:21.961
[both grunting]

44:22.096 --> 44:25.564
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

44:25.699 --> 44:27.099
[gunshot]

44:27.101 --> 44:30.236
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

44:30.371 --> 44:32.237
- [grunts]

44:32.239 --> 44:34.506
[both groan]

44:34.508 --> 44:41.647
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

44:47.655 --> 44:49.121
- Put the gun down.

44:49.256 --> 44:51.791
- [breathing heavily]

44:51.925 --> 44:55.928
- Put the gun down

44:56.063 --> 44:58.231
or he dies.
